#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:2
msgid "Model Context Protocol (MCP) — Ticket Server"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:5
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:7
msgid ""
"Loonflow exposes a **Model Context Protocol** server that lets compatible"
" clients (for example AI-assisted editors) query and handle tickets "
"through authenticated tools. The server name advertised to clients is "
"``loonflow-ticket``. Tools call the same permission-aware ticket services"
" as the web UI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:10
msgid "Authentication"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:12
msgid ""
"Calls must be authenticated with an **access token**. Supported token "
"types include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:14
msgid ""
"**Personal access token** (recommended for MCP clients): values start "
"with ``lfpat.``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:15
msgid "**JWT** issued by Loonflow (same as API usage)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:17
msgid ""
"You can pass the token in the MCP HTTP client as a header (see "
"configuration below), pass it per tool where supported, or configure a "
"server-side environment variable for non-interactive setups."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:20
msgid "Create a personal access token"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:22
msgid ""
"Open **Personal Information** in the product UI, then open **Personal "
"Access Token**. Create a new token and store it securely. Replace ``xxx``"
" in the configuration example with that token."
msgstr ""

