#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:39
msgid "Client configuration (example)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:41
msgid ""
"Use the Streamable HTTP endpoint exposed by the MCP process (default path"
" ``/mcp``). Adjust host and port to match your deployment; local "
"development often uses port ``8002``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:56
msgid ""
"Replace ``xxx`` with your **personal access token**. If the client "
"supports separate auth configuration, you may alternatively send ``X"
"-Loonflow-Access-Token`` with the raw token value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:59
msgid "Supported tools"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:61
msgid "The server currently registers the following tools."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:64
msgid "``ticket_list``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:66
msgid ""
"Returns a **paginated ticket list** for the authenticated user, including"
" total count and pagination metadata."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:68 ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:89
msgid "**Main behavior:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:70
msgid ""
"**category** selects which list to query: ``duty`` (my todo), ``owner`` "
"(created by me), ``relation`` (related to me), ``view`` (I can view), "
"``worked`` (tickets I processed), ``intervene`` (I can intervene), "
"``all`` (all tickets; **admin only**)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:71
msgid ""
"Optional filters include free-text **search_value**, **create_start** / "
"**create_end**, **workflow_ids**, **node_ids**, **ticket_ids**, "
"**act_state**, **creator_id**, **parent_ticket_id**, **reverse**, "
"**per_page**, and **page**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:72
msgid ""
"If neither ``create_start`` nor ``create_end`` is set, a default time "
"window is applied (see server implementation)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:75
msgid "``ticket_detail``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:77
msgid ""
"Loads **ticket detail** for a given ``ticket_id``: dynamic form schema "
"(**component_info_list**), workflow metadata, **field_permissions**, "
"derived **required_fields** / **optional_fields** / **readonly_fields**, "
"and available **actions** (plus **admin_actions** when applicable), "
"including base node identifiers used by some actions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:80
msgid "``ticket_prepare_handle``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:82
msgid ""
"Prepares the **same context as ticket detail** (form schema, permissions,"
" and available actions). Use it when you want a dedicated “prepare to "
"handle” step before submitting an action."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:85
msgid "``ticket_handle``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:87
msgid ""
"**Executes a workflow action** on a ticket after permission and field "
"validation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:91
msgid ""
"**action_type** and **action_id** must match one of the actions returned "
"for the current user (including admin actions when allowed)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:92
msgid "**fields** must satisfy **required** fields for the current node/form."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:93
msgid ""
"**action_props** carries extra properties required by specific actions "
"(for example node context for comments when applicable)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:94
msgid ""
"**dry_run**: when ``true``, validates the request and returns a summary "
"**without** changing the ticket; when ``false``, performs the handle "
"operation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:97
msgid "Operational notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:99
msgid ""
"Default listen address and port are controlled by environment variables "
"(for example ``LOONFLOW_MCP_HOST``, ``LOONFLOW_MCP_PORT``); align your "
"client URL with the running process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api_reference/mcp.rst:100
msgid ""
"For server-side default authentication (for example stdio transports), "
"refer to ``LOONFLOW_MCP_ACCESS_TOKEN`` in the MCP server documentation in"
" the codebase."
msgstr ""

